# ----------------------------------------------------------
# INPUTS COMMON TO BOTH CASES
# ----------------------------------------------------------
# alpha = one-sided significance level.
# treat_response_A = true treatment response (treatment A) [proportion].
# treat_response_B = true treatment response (treatment B) [proportion].
# baseline_response = baseline response in control group [proportion].
# n_arm = arm size.
# ----------------------------------------------------------

# ----------------------------------------------------------
# 1.A. Treatments A and B entering at the same time i.e.
# control completely shared.
# ----------------------------------------------------------

# ----------------------------------------------------------
# Function name: gen_platform_a
#
# Case specific parameters:
#
# n_arm = number of patients per treatment arm
# correction: if "bonferroni", performs bonferroni correction.
#             default is unadjusted
# ----------------------------------------------------------

# ----------------------------------------------------------
# 1.B: Treatments A and B start at different times i.e. 
# control shared but not completely.
# ----------------------------------------------------------

# ----------------------------------------------------------
# Function name: gen_platform_b
#
# Case specific parameters:
# 
# Considering the sections in time:
# A1: Treat A x Control / A2: treat A x Treat B x Control / A3: Treat B x control
# (For further detailing on A1, A2, A3, refer to sketch). 
# n_A1 = Number of patients on each arm in time section A1
# n_A2 = Number of patients on each arm in time section A2
# n_A3 = Number of patients on each arm in time section A3
# correction = Performs the imputed alpha correction. 
#              Options are: "lond", "bonferroni", "unadjusted" (default).
# ----------------------------------------------------------


